example.p:
Similarly, if we began with f(x) = x^2 - 1, then the transformation
\frac{1}{2}f(x) \amp= \frac{1}{2}(x^2 - 1) \amp= \frac{1}{2}x^2 - \frac{1}{2}
would be just like f(x), but all of its output values would be multiplied by \frac{1}{2}.

